<subSubSection id="EBCDF5AB7735FFF4FF4EFEE70E634B9A" pageId="14" pageNumber="395" type="description">
<paragraph id="A368A6207735FFF4FF4EFEE70FB34BBE" blockId="14.[151,1436,350,666]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis id="91A37A327735FFF4FF4EFEE70A184B07" bold="true" box="[151,297,350,376]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Description.</emphasis>
Pale yellow with strongly developed dark pattern on head, pro-, and mesonotum (
<figureCitation id="3BECBAA57735FFF4FB66FEE60E224B06" box="[1215,1299,351,377]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–47" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1997,2021]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,535,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-133@11.[174,1412,525,1974]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–47. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404167/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
). Forewings transparent with two dark spots or stripes at level of transverse vein of clavus and in basal part of subapical cells; in light specimens these spots reduced. Basal part of claval veins white, all other veins dark.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A368A6207735FFF4FF1EFE720E634B9A" blockId="14.[151,1436,350,666]" box="[199,1362,458,486]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
One of the largest 
<taxonomicName id="64D7DDA37735FFF4FE4CFE72093B4B9B" authorityName="Lewis" authorityYear="1836" box="[405,522,459,484]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macropsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="91A37A327735FFF4FE4CFE72093B4B9B" box="[405,522,459,484]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Macropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, body length (including tegmina): 
<specimenCount id="B5D16DA97735FFF4FC30FE720F314B9A" box="[1001,1024,459,485]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 
<quantity id="642F0BC57735FFF4FBD5FE730FA74B9A" box="[1036,1174,458,485]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="14" pageNumber="395" unit="mm" value="4.4" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.3">4.3–4.5 mm</quantity>
; 
<specimenCount id="B5D16DA97735FFF4FB78FE720F874B9A" box="[1185,1206,459,485]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, 5.0– 
<quantity id="642F0BC57735FFF4FB2FFE730E7F4B9A" box="[1270,1358,458,485]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="395" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
