</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBCDF5AB7735FFF4FF1EFDAB0E51482E" pageId="14" pageNumber="395" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A368A6207735FFF4FF1EFDAB0E51482E" blockId="14.[151,1436,350,666]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis id="91A37A327735FFF4FF1EFDAB0A504853" bold="true" box="[199,353,530,556]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Distribution.</emphasis>
Eastern half of North Caucasus, mountains of Southern 
<collectingCountry id="DBC0E6B07735FFF4FC14FDAA0F614852" box="[973,1104,531,557]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
and Central Asia, South Siberia eastwards to Tyva, 
<collectingCountry id="DBC0E6B07735FFF4FE4AFD8E0935482E" box="[403,516,567,593]" name="Mongolia" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
. In Southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="DBC0E6B07735FFF4FD1DFD8E0876482E" box="[708,839,567,593]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
was found only on Dzhungarsky Alatau Range.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBCDF5AB7735FFF4FF1EFDE2090848E5" pageId="14" pageNumber="395" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A368A6207735FFF4FF1EFDE2090848E5" blockId="14.[151,1436,350,666]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
